  "text": "QUART 1 resembles the basic result of [CITATION_1] . They showed that if the home and foreign firm engage in a one-shot Cournot game, then an export subsidy is optimal. This result has subsequently been shown to be sensitive to a relaxation of many of the model's assumptions (a fact of which The Economist is clearly aware).",
